---
import CaseStudy from '../../components/CaseStudy.astro';
---

<CaseStudy
  title="Drone Package Delivery Mechanism"
  description="Mechanical payload release and delivery mechanism for a drone package delivery system. Two-person team design project, MEGN 261, Fall 2025."
  backHref="/#projects"
  backLabel="Back to Projects"
  eyebrow="MEGN 261 Design Project"
>

  <h2>Problem</h2>
  <p>
    Design a mechanical release and delivery mechanism for a drone-based package delivery system.
    The mechanism needed to reliably hold a payload in flight and release it at a target location
    without requiring active user control of the release event.
  </p>

  <h2>Approach</h2>
  <p>
    Two-person team design project focused on mechanical simplicity and reliable actuation.
    The design process moved from functional requirements through concept generation to a final
    design with supporting documentation.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Requirements definition:</strong> Established payload hold strength, release
      reliability, and form factor constraints based on the target drone platform.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Concept development:</strong> Evaluated multiple release mechanism concepts
      (gravity, servo, magnetic) before selecting the final approach based on reliability
      and weight budget.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>CAD and documentation:</strong> Full SolidWorks model and assembly drawings
      produced for the selected design. Final design presented via poster format.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Results</h2>
  <table class="results-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Deliverable</th>
        <th>Status</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>SolidWorks CAD assembly</td>
        <td class="mono">Complete</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Final design poster</td>
        <td class="mono">Complete</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Final design presentation</td>
        <td class="mono">Complete</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>My Role</h2>
  <p>
    Co-designed with a partner. Contributed to concept generation, CAD modeling, and
    presentation preparation in equal parts.
  </p>

